main event: A bright red object was spotted in the sky southwest of Clinton, Indiana on November 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object had spokes in the center and was red around the edges.
The object was observed for 10 minutes at an altitude of approximately 3,000 to 10,000 feet.
A temperature inversion was reported in the area between 1,500 feet and 10,000 feet.
No conclusions were made based on the preliminary evidence.
sighted object: a bright red object with spokes in the center
